records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 2, PTC deliver heroin.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1 and 3.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend ten (10) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing immediately;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
6) Pay court costs including the $90.00 buy money to Metro Drug;
7) Provide DNA sample;
8) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
9) maintain absolute sobriety.
Minutes.
